HEADWORD: Telepathy
<hw>Te*lep"a*thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ far off
+ <?/, <?/, to suffer.]</ety> <def>The sympathetic affection of one mind
by the thoughts, feelings, or emotions of another at a distance, without
communication through the ordinary channels of sensation.</def>
<note>The existence of this ability has not been proven
scientifically.</note>-- <wordforms><wf>Tel`e*path"ic</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos> -- <wf>Te*lep"a*thist</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Telepheme</ent>⟦br⟧
